text: Gabriella Juhász (born 19 March 1985 in Kisvárda) is a retired Hungarian handballer. Juhász made her international debut on 3 March 2007 against Norway, and participated on the 2009 World Championship. ==Achievements== *Nemzeti Bajnokság I: **Winner: 2005, 2006 **Silver Medallist: 2004, 2007, 2010, 2011 **Bronze Medallist: 2008 *Magyar Kupa: **Winner: 2005, 2006, 2007 **Silver Medallist: 2004, 2011 *Liga Naţională: **Silver Medallist: 2009 *EHF Champions League: **Semifinalist: 2007 *EHF Women's Cup Winners' Cup: **Finalist: 2006 *EHF Cup: **Finalist: 2004, 2005 *Norwegian League **Bronze: 2017/2018 *Norwegian Cup: **Finalist: 2018, 2019 == References == Category:1985 births Category:Living people Category:People from Kisvárda Category:Hungarian female handball players Category:Győri Audi ETO KC players Category:Hungarian expatriate sportspeople in Romania
